Uses of Interface
model.IMove

  • Packages that use IMove 
    Package Description
    model  

    • Uses of IMove in model

      Classes in model that implement IMove 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  ClearMove
      A ClearMove operates on a single NumberTileContainer Clearing the tile removes the number, and then the board should settle.
      class  RearrangeMove
      Rearrange moves clear all non-null, non-empty, non-six tiles on the board and replace them with new randomly generated tiles Sixes are never replaced because it can make Release levels unwinnable
      class  SwapMove
      A swap move swaps two adjacent tiles on the board Only non-empty, non-null tiles can be swapped Once two tiles are added, the move is valid and should be run
      class  UserMove
      UserMove is the basic move type for the SixesWild game They are the only way to score points or mark tiles in Elimination rounds A valid UserMove is 2 or more adjacent tiles that sum to 6
      Methods in model with parameters of type IMove 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void PuzzleLevel.react(IMove move) 
      void Level.react(IMove move)
      After every move, the board settles the tiles.
      void EliminationLevel.react(IMove move)
      UserMoves and RearrangeMoves use up one move If the move is a valid UserMove, it also markes all tiles in that move
      void ReleaseLevel.react(IMove move)
      UserMoves and RearrangeMoves us up one moveRemaining, that is the only effect on the level
